.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-WATCH" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.24" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-watch \- Watch a tracked job in a live terminal UI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose watch [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Open a live watch view for a tracked job. On TTYs this uses the alternate\-screen watch UI; otherwise it falls back to line\-oriented scheduler and log streaming.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to watch instead of the latest recorded submission.
.TP
\fB--service\fR \fISERVICE\fR
Service to focus initially in the watch UI.
.TP
\fB--lines\fR \fILINES\fR
Number of trailing log lines to seed into the watch view. Default: 100.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose watch \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose watch \-f compose.yaml \-\-service app
hpc\-compose watch \-f compose.yaml \-\-job\-id 12345 \-\-lines 200
.fi
